      "subtasks": [],
      "created": "2014-05-09T23:54:41.589+0000",
      "description": "Performance of MR2 jobs falls drastically as YARN config parameter yarn.nodemanager.resource.memory-mb  is increased beyond a certain value. \n\nPerformance of Spark falls drastically as the value of yarn.nodemanager.resource.memory-mb is decreased beyond a certain value for a large data set.\n\nThis makes it hard to co-locate MR2 and Spark jobs in YARN.\n\nThe experiments are being conducted on a 6-node cluster. The following workloads are being run: TeraGen, TeraSort, TeraValidate, WordCount, ShuffleText and PageRank.\n\nWill add more details to this JIRA over time.\n",
      "priority": {
        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/priority/3",
        "iconUrl": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg",
        "name": "Major",
        "id": "3"
