          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12713424/comment/14001327",
            "id": "14001327",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=nravi",
              "name": "nravi",
              "key": "nravi",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Nishkam Ravi",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
            },
            "body": "Experiments were done with FIFO and Fair schedulers under two different settings: single-job and multi-job modes. \nIn the single-job mode, one instance of a workload executes in the cluster at a time. In the multi-job mode, multiple instances (10 in this case) of the same job are spawned and execute in parallel on the cluster. This is done for six different workloads. Average run time is measured and reported.\n\nPerformance drop was observed with FIFO in both single-job and multi-job modes (at the time of opening this JIRA). And has been verified. Fair scheduler performs fine even with increased container size. \n\nFair to conclude that FIFO was the problem. No problem with co-locating MR2 and Spark jobs using Fair scheduler.  Will try Capacity scheduler as well while we are at it. ",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=nravi",
              "name": "nravi",
              "key": "nravi",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Nishkam Ravi",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
            },
            "created": "2014-05-19T01:49:40.359+0000",
            "updated": "2014-05-19T01:49:40.359+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12713424/comment/14011844",
            "id": "14011844",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=nravi",
              "name": "nravi",
              "key": "nravi",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Nishkam Ravi",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
            },
            "body": "Unlike FIFO, whose performance deteriorates consistently across multiple benchmarks as value of yarn.nodemanager.resource.memory-mb is increased from 16GB to 40GB, Capacity scheduler performs well for all benchmarks except for TeraValidate. \n\nFor TeraValidate in single-job mode:\n\nExec. time with Fair: 38 sec (yarn.nodemanager.resource.memory-mb = 16GB)\nExec. time with Fair: 38 sec (yarn.nodemanager.resource.memory-mb = 40GB)\nExec. time with Capacity: 51 sec (yarn.nodemanager.resource.memory-mb = 16GB)\nExec. time with Capacity: 100 sec (yarn.nodemanager.resource.memory-mb = 40GB)\n\nAlso, in multi-job mode, Capacity seems to be behaving like FIFO. Scheduling one job at a time for execution. \n",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=nravi",
              "name": "nravi",
              "key": "nravi",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Nishkam Ravi",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
            },
            "created": "2014-05-28T23:53:32.593+0000",
            "updated": "2014-05-28T23:53:32.593+0000"
          },
          {
